`nvim/lua/` is the Lua-side runtime for a Neovim plugin whose build artifacts come from this repo's TypeScript compiler (`src/snippet.ts`). Depending on this directory means loading the `steno-ts` plugin via its single entry point, `M.setup(opts)`; there is no other public surface, and no code here executes except through that call and the autocmds it installs.

The subtree currently has exactly one child, `steno-ts/`, which is the entire implementation — a single `init.lua` with no internal cross-file coupling. The only coupling that matters crosses the repo boundary: `init.lua` and `src/snippet.ts` must agree on the `"@@"` sentinel format and the JSON snippet-table schema, since the Lua side only consumes what the TS side emits. That agreement is undocumented by any type system on this side, so a schema or fence-format change in the TS compiler requires a matching edit here, and there's no compiler error to catch a mismatch — expansion just stops silently.

No intent.md exists for this directory, so there's nothing to check for divergence.